    "recap_headline": "University of Washington",
    "recap_text": "LOS ANGELES \u2013\nWashington dropped the first of three games against No. 13 USC, falling to the Trojans 5-0 on Friday night.\nWashington moves to 9-12 on the season and 4-3 in Big Ten play.\nThe Huskies held USC to just six hits on the day and only three earned runs, but couldn't find the run support to back the defensive effort.\nNoah Kenney\nmade the start for Washington, throwing 5.1 innings while allowing six hits, three earned runs, and striking out three batters.\nTommy Brandenburg\nclosed out the day for the Huskies with 2.2 innings of no-hit ball.\nWashington struggled to get the offense going against one of the best pitchers in the nation in Mason Edwards.\nDaniel Porras\nand\nColton Bower\neach tallied singles in the game.\nThe Huskies will look to bounce back on Saturday night in game two of the series.\nJackson Thomas\nwill get the ball as the two teams face off again at 7 p.m. in Los Angeles.\nDAWG BITES\nWashington's three-game win streak came to a close on Friday night at USC\nNoah Kenney\ntossed 5.1 innings on Friday night, extending his streak to six straight appearances of at least 4.1 innings pitched\nFor news, scores, highlights and more,\ndownload the Go Huskies app\non your mobile device. Follow @UW_Baseball\u00a0on\nInstagram\n,\nX\n,\nThreads\n, and\nFacebook\nand subscribe to\nUW Athletics on YouTube\nfor the latest on the Dawgs.",
